1
00:00:06,010 --> 00:00:08,706
Sincerity means appreciation
for the truth.

2
00:00:08,830 --> 00:00:10,849
[GPS of Sincerity]

3
00:00:10,849 --> 00:00:13,741
So otherwise, yes, 
in a general sense,
 

4
00:00:13,741 --> 00:00:17,232
Guru Mahārāj also pointed, 
you can have a sincere criminal;

5
00:00:17,232 --> 00:00:19,151
he’s very sincere 
about what he’s doing,
 

6
00:00:19,151 --> 00:00:22,031
and he cares about his boss,
and their group,

7
00:00:22,031 --> 00:00:27,401
and he’s loyal, he’s willing 
to sacrifice for the group, and …

8
00:00:27,401 --> 00:00:31,819
So that’s a relative
application of sincerity,
 

9
00:00:31,819 --> 00:00:36,169
but when we speak about it
in a more refined sense,

10
00:00:36,169 --> 00:00:39,011
it will be demonstrated ...

11
00:00:39,011 --> 00:00:42,706
Otherwise you can have 
a sincere Nazi,
 

12
00:00:42,706 --> 00:00:48,083
who pays their bills on time,
who loves children …

13
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:52,336
So, really sincerity 
has to be viewed

14
00:00:52,336 --> 00:00:55,836
in terms of relation to the truth, 
what the truth is.

15
00:00:55,836 --> 00:00:58,147
So, if someone rightly says,
“Well, I don’t know”.

16
00:00:58,147 --> 00:01:00,866
Alright then, that doesn’t mean
that nobody knows.

17
00:01:00,866 --> 00:01:02,396
Like sometimes 
[people say], 
 

18
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:04,466
“Well, no one knows.”
No, it’s not that no one knows,

19
00:01:04,466 --> 00:01:08,455
nobody you know knows,
would be more accurate.

20
00:01:08,455 --> 00:01:09,738
There maybe someone
who knows.

21
00:01:09,738 --> 00:01:12,498
Just you and those you know
do not know.

22
00:01:12,498 --> 00:01:14,556
Don’t say that nobody knows.

23
00:01:15,796 --> 00:01:19,603
So then, as Prabhupād would say
in the Bhagavad-gītā,

24
00:01:19,603 --> 00:01:25,149
“That person, who realises that
material life, material existence

25
00:01:25,149 --> 00:01:30,707
is a source of perplexity 
at every step,
 

26
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:34,177
it behooves such a person

27
00:01:34,177 --> 00:01:39,317
to approach a spiritual master,
and take guidance.”

28
00:01:40,131 --> 00:01:42,299
We take guidance 
for everything.

29
00:01:42,299 --> 00:01:47,246
Everybody watching us or many
people watching, they have GPS.

30
00:01:48,399 --> 00:01:50,793
They are not opposed
to taking guidance, why?

31
00:01:50,793 --> 00:01:53,023
Because they 
understand the value—

32
00:01:53,023 --> 00:01:59,116
this device will give indicators
of how I should proceed.

33
00:01:59,116 --> 00:02:01,564
So for us, you say,
a sincere person,
 

34
00:02:01,564 --> 00:02:06,464
a spiritually progressive person—
they need spiritual GPS,

35
00:02:06,464 --> 00:02:09,826
which comes in the form
of what we call

36
00:02:09,826 --> 00:02:11,590
sādhu, śāstra,
guru, Vaiṣṇava,

37
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:16,560
means spiritual teachers, 
the spiritual books, spiritual practitioners.

38
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:20,960
You come in connection with them, 
put yourself under their guidance,

39
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:25,014
and then that Revealed Truth
expressed by them,

40
00:02:25,014 --> 00:02:32,086
becomes like a magnetic North 
by which you can navigate

41
00:02:32,086 --> 00:02:33,766
the world and existence.

